      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AVOID THE NOISE (4) flew the lids and led throughout to get off the mark with his maiden win, then finished a nose second last start at this track over 366m (19.87). Returns to the course where he won his maiden. Racing well and looks a leading chance again. ANTI VENOM (1) is yet to miss the placings in an excellent record this trip which boasts two wins and two placings. Below best last time at Q Parklands (30.50) in a Grade 6, finishing a 10 length fourth. Looks one of the chances. MOCKERY MIRAGE (2) finished third (22.45) two back at Q Lakeside but out of the placings last time when 6th there. Has a good record here at this journey. Should be about the mark. OCEAN ART (8) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
